The paper discusses the Iterated Prisoner's Dilemma, which is a classic game theory problem and falls under the category of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the performance of different strategies, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of features on the success of strategies, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of strategies in tournaments, which could fall under the category of computer science and society (cs.CY).
